ow-entropy r-process. The\nlow explosion energy and nucleosynthetic implications are compatible with the\nobserved properties of the Crab supernova, and the small nickel mass supports\nthe possibility that our models explain some subluminous Type II-P supernovae.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 2 Dec 2005 17:38:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 2 Jan 2006 14:05:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-08-09"}
